  "seoDescription": "Quantum computers are uniquely poised to carry out highly efficient search and estimation algorithms. Iterative quantum amplitude estimation is one such example, in which quantum-classical hybrid methods are used to estimate the probability of a certain state being measured in a data set. This demo explores the methodology and implementation of this method in PennyLane",
